rComments: Caring and a nice person, especially compared to other professors. However, this is a class that you only use to get the credit and get out, so don't listen a lot to the powerpoints, because much of it is nonsense anyways. Almost nothing you learn will EVER be used in your future. Do take it since it's easier reading than writing (in my opinion)
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Avoid her if you can... Nice person but a very bad prof. disorganized, all over the place, unclear projects. I was miserable in this class, and I usually LOVE french. BAD.

I had her as a TA last semester and I really liked her. She is a kind-hearted individual and means her best. However, her teaching style isn't suited for a large class like FRA1720. Her ways of engaging the students aren't really efficient and it makes for a dull class. The class is easy and she is nice, she just wasn't the best prof.

French isn't her first language and it shows: she makes mistakes while speaking and the TA's have to correct her because she doesn't know the projects we have to do. She cares about her students but it doesn't make up for the lack of knowledge of the subject.

Je me sens mitigée face à cette prof. Le français n'est que sa langue tierce et en tant que francophone de souche, il est plutôt douloureux de se faire enseigner par qqun qui ne connait pas sa matière. Elle nous enseignait et les assistants devaient la corriger puisqu'elle ne connaissait même pas la matière qu'elle nous demandait d'apprendre.
La prof est correct. Elle s'assure que tout le monde comprenne le cours. Honnêtement, la présence n'est pas nécessaire. Il y a beaucoup de travaux et de lectures, mais ce n'est trop difficile.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: She is in fact not that fun of a lecturer and missing a few classes will not affect your grade at all tbh, but she does care about whether you understand or not. I wouldn't necessarily recommend her, but she's alright.

She is not a bad person, and I feel bad for my rating, but I don't have a choice. You don't have to show up to class most of the time, she almost never uses her mic when she teaches in a big classroom, which makes it hard to hear her. Also, there are many mistakes in her slideshows.
difficile à comprendre et inutile daller au class
